               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" from="1737" to="1738">1737/'38</date>
                  <ab type="history">The church of Nārgā Śǝllāse is located on the islet of
                        <placeName ref="LOC4969Narga">Nārgā</placeName>, east of <placeName ref="LOC2522Daq">Daq</placeName> island in the middle of lake <placeName ref="LOC5888Tana">Ṭānā</placeName>. It was founded in <date from="1737" to="1738">1737/'38</date> by <roleName type="title">ʾǝtege</roleName>
                     <persName ref="PRS2682BerhanM">Mǝntǝwwāb</persName> and this event is described
                     in the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2624ZenaNa">Zenā Nārgā</ref>. The
                     construction of the entire complex took up to <date when="1750">1750</date> and
                     the church was endowed by <persName ref="PRS2682BerhanM">Mǝntǝwwāb</persName>
                     and her son <persName ref="PRS5617IyasuII">ʾIyāsu II</persName> with books and
                     liturgical objects. The church was partially restored in the <date from="1950" to="1960">1950s</date> under <persName ref="PRS5226haylase">Ḫāyla Śǝllāse
                        I</persName>.</ab>
                  <ab type="description">Nārgā Śǝllāse is a round centrally-planned church of stones
                     and lime located at the centre of a compound. The church was adorned with
                     engravings on wood and stone and with murals on the external walls. Some parts
                     of the church were later repainted.</ab>
               </note>
            </place>
